Angel Fire's Oso High XC Race
Las Campanas 2015 New Mexico Regional Road Race Championships
The Glory Days XC MTB Race
description: Glorieta Camps is proud to present its first Cross Country mountain bike race. After great successes in cyclocross, XTERRA, and Enduro, we are ready to dive into the great world of XC MTB! The biggest item to note is our introduction of a UCI race open to all pro's and Category 1 racers, even a U23 category! So, spread the word because this is a race and a course that is truly worth the drive!
course: Get ready for a course that has never been raced before! We are presenting two unique courses this year with a CAT 1/2/3 Course and then a special UCI style course for the pro's!
registration: Registration is available online until July 24 at 10:00 PM. Registration is available through New Mexico Sports Online.
notes: A food truck will be present for all food needs, bike wash station provided, and lodging available for Saturday night so you can be well rested for the race!
directions: I-25 North, Exit 299, Turn left over bridge, turn left onto State Rd 50, proceed to the guard gate.

NM Spokettes Women's CX Clinic
description:
New Mexico Spokettes Racing Team and JBV coaching present:
Women's CycloCross Clinic
Sunday September 27, 2015
9am-Noon
course: Burton Park, Nob Hill Albuquerque, NM
registration: Cost: $0, donations accepted, USAC annual or one-day license required ($10)
notes:
What Will Be Covered:
1. Dismounting & Remounting, including “3 Points of Contact”, the “Suitcase”, and shouldering the bike: when and how
2. Cornering: How to set up for a corner, proper line choice, pairing corners
3. Off cambered cornering and sand cornering.
4. Run ups and stairs: How to negotiate these with skill and grace
5. Starts!

title: The Dragon Slayer Classic at White Mesa
Desert Academy CX race presented by Sport Systems
Glorieta Camps Cyclocross Weekend
description: Bring out the family for a weekend filled with fun, Halloween festivities, and plenty of racing to keep everyone busy. We will be racing under the lights for Halloween on Saturday to spice things up and then on Sunday we will be racing the best and longest course Glorieta has ever assembled. Plenty of lodging available with food trucks present on Saturday night.
course: There will be two courses for the weekend! On Halloween night, we will keep it short and sweet with a 2.5km course with a lot of the favorite sections. The course will be lit for a great race! On Sunday, the course will lengthen out to 3.5km to ensure that we get every bit of the Glorieta course in there with a few new features to add to the list! Overall, come enjoy New Mexico's best cyclocross cross!! The course will run the same direction both days but will have additions on Sunday.
registration: Registration is available online until October 29th and then onsite registration will be available with a $10 fee.
directions: I-25 Northbound, Exit 299, turn left over the highway, turn left at the T, enter through the gated access point.
